<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-15T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="573" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/2741: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-15T16:00:00+01:00">January 15, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 9:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>19. My 18, January 14, 4 p.m. French and British have also cancelled
                                permissions their troops. Belief among middle class Arabs and
                                workers is that Nationalist movement is supported and backed by
                                United States Government. Consulate considers this belief encouraged
                                by ill-considered actions of officers mentioned in my despatch 1186
                                November 22<note n="42" xml:id="d573fn42">Not printed.</note> and by
                                over friendly attitude of former U.S. general officers here. French
                                are taking precautions but do not intend to interfere unless native
                                demonstrations become disorderly.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Algiers as my 5, to Tangier as 6 and true reading to
                                Rabat.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>